{{Use Australian English|date=October 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = protected | name = Aldinga Scrub Conservation Park | state = sa | iucn_category = III | image = Sellicks range.JPG | caption = Reserve as viewed from Seagull Street, [[Aldinga Beach, South Australia|Aldinga Beach]] | image_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|35|17|38|S|138|27|21|E|display=inline,title}} | force_national_map = | relief = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | map_alt = | nearest_town_or_city = [[Adelaide city centre|Adelaide]] | area = 2.66 | area_footnotes = <ref name=ReserveList>{{cite web|title=Protected Areas Information System - reserve list (as of 17 Feb 2014)|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/b88e6e26-4bd9-4c68-8fff-9e800114eb69/park-management-protected-areas-gen.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment Water and Natural Resources|accessdate=26 March 2014|pages=}}</ref> | established = 7 November 1975<ref name=ReserveList/> | established_footnotes = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_footnotes = | managing_authorities = [[Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources (South Australia)|Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources]] | url = http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/parks/Find_a_Park/Browse_by_region/Fleurieu_Peninsula/Aldinga_Scrub_Conservation_Park }}
'''Aldinga Scrub Conservation Park''' is a [[protected area]] located in the suburbs of [[Aldinga Beach, South Australia|Aldinga Beach]] and [[Sellicks Beach, South Australia|Sellicks Beach]] about {{convert|46|km|abbr=off}} south by west of [[Adelaide city centre|Adelaide]] in [[South Australia]]. The park was proclaimed in November 1975 under the ''[[National Parks and Wildlife Act 1972]]'' for the purpose of protecting a parcel of undeveloped land considered to be 'a significant remnant of the natural habitat that once occurred all along the southern Adelaide coastline'. The conservation park is classified as an [[International Union for Conservation of Nature|IUCN]] [[IUCN protected area categories#Category III — Natural Monument or Feature|Category III protected area]].<ref name=gazateer>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name= Aldinga Scrub Conservation Park |feature= SA0000687 }}</ref><ref name=MP>{{Citation | author1=South Australia. Department of Environment and Planning Far West District | author2=South Australia. National Parks and Wildlife Service | title=Aldinga Scrub Conservation Park management plan, Eyre Peninsula, South Australia | publication-date=1992 | publisher=Dept. of Environment and Planning | url= http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/b794cd0d-1e6c-4d60-8bbf-9ef000e5f62d/cons-gen-aldingascrubparkmgmtplan-adopted.pdf| page= 5}}</ref><ref name=CAPAD2012SASum>{{cite web|title=CAPAD 2012 South Australia Summary (see 'DETAIL' tab)|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/pages/0f927a4e-336a-490c-a896-ec37874a5c73/files/capad2012sa.xlsx|work=CAPAD 2012|publisher=Australian Government - Department of the Environment|accessdate=6 February 2014|date=6 February 2014}}</ref>
