[[File:Countries by pear production in 2016.png|thumb|550px|Countries by pear production in 2016]] This is a '''list of countries by [[pear]] production''' in 2016, based on data from the [[Food and Agriculture Organization Corporate Statistical Database]].<ref>{{citeweb|website=FAOSTAT|title=Crops|url=http://www.fao.org/faostat/en/#data/QC/|access-date=6 September 2018}} Countries - Select All; Regions - World + (Total); Elements - Production Quantity; Items - Pears + Pears, dry; Years - 2016</ref> The total world production for pears in 2016 was 41,709,029 [[Tonne|metric tonnes]].<ref group="n">Sum of production of 'pears' and 'pears, dry', according to [[Food and Agriculture Organization Corporate Statistical Database|FAOSTAT]].</ref> China was by far the largest producer, accounting for 49.3% of world production.
