'''Rudeš''' is a neighbourhood of the city of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]], within the [[Trešnjevka – sjever]] district. The area covered by the local city council Rudeš has a population of 9,725 (2011).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zagreb.hr/default.aspx?id=13933|title=7. Mjesni odbor Rudeš|work=zagreb.hr|publisher=City of Zagreb|language=hr|accessdate=5 November 2016}}</ref>

There is a small [[Salesian]] church in the neighbourhood, called "The Church of St.Anne".

In Rudeš, there is also an elementary school called "Elementary school Rudeš".<ref>[http://www.os-rudes-zg.skole.hr/ The official web-page of Elementary school Rudeš]</ref>

A soccer team that is currently in the first Croatian soccer league and is from Rudeš is called [[NK Rudeš]].<ref>[http://www.nk-rudes.hr/index_hr.php The official web-page of Soccer Club Rudeš]</ref>

